linear
Linear (append) mode
Combine the hard disk partitions by simply appending one to the other
0
RAID-0 (striping) mode
Combine the hard disk partitions into one logical device so as to fill them up evenly 
1
RAID-1 (mirroring) mode
N disk drives which are exact copies of each other. Protects against failure of (N - 1) drives.
4
RAID-4/5 mode
N drives,C MB per drive, provides C*(N - 1) MB.Protects against failure of a single drive. Parity blocks stored on a single drive 
5
RAID-4/5 mode
Similar to RAID 4 except parity blocks are distributed across all the drives 

